tip.text: Yummy, sambal veg at Absolute Malacca...
Nice rojak Ayam but I wish the portion was a bit bigger for the price of RM7.50 per plate

formattedAddress: Batu Lintang Hawker Centre (Jalan Batu Lintang)

tip.text: This restaurant has the Royal look... Nice variety of Indian dishes offered here. Great place to go for lunch or dinner. Tried the cheesy naan, Ayam Penyet and mutton curry here
Was excited to hear of another newly opened cafe in town... Check out Kai Joo Cafe - located along the lane where the famous meat pie and yam puffs are sold. It's just next to the Police Station.

formattedAddress: Ground Floor, 29 (Kai Joo Lane Lane Building)

tip.text: A newly opened cafe to hang out with your friends.. Love the ambience and the matcha cake here.. This cafe has another another floor and alfresco seats for you to do people watching..
Nice place to hang out with friends over tea and yummy cakes.. Love the red velvet here
Love the huge beef burger with bacon here.. Comes with fries and a regular sized soft drink
I love shopping at this mall... Was pleasantly surprised to see a new cafe opened recently here. You can hv charsiew rice, Kampua, Rojak, mixed rice etc here
Love the strategic location of this hotel near the city centre. Can get reasonable room rates which comes with free breakfast! The night market is located nearby too!
Always been my favourite market. I can easily get kong pia, three layer pork, charsiew, crispy apam Balik and even nice clothes here at reasonable prices!

formattedAddress: Shop No. 8, Level 3, Majma' Tuanku Abdul Halim Mu'adzam Shah (Jalan P. Ramlee)
location.address: Shop No. 8, Level 3, Majma' Tuanku Abdul Halim Mu'adzam Shah

tip.text: My first visit to this kopitiam. Heard the one at Jalan Song served tastier food. The local kuih here is not bad. Lots of variety of food found here- Taiwan beef noodles, porridge, Kueh chap etc..

formattedAddress: Tabuan Tranquility Commercial Centre, Jalan Canna
location.address: Tabuan Tranquility Commercial Centre, Jalan Canna

tip.text: Great place to get laksa, Kueh chap and even Foochow gong pia!
Great place to try cheap Thai food! You can get a bowl of yummy Tom yam for only RM6!
Nice soupy vegetarian noodles served here. Huge portion too! Yum2
I like the variety of food found here... Lots of tables and seats available too..

formattedAddress: NU Sentral (Lot L3.14, Level 3), Jalan Tun Sambanthan
location.address: NU Sentral (Lot L3.14, Level 3), Jalan Tun Sambanthan

tip.text: The yam cakes here are nice but a bit sticky for my taste. The price is a bit steep too. Rm8.90 for four pcs.
The fried chicken nasi lemak is sooo mouthwatering here! Really whetted my appetite and I finished the whole plate within 20 mins.
Enjoyed the spaghetti bolognese here with friends! My advice is to go during lunch and your meal comes with a free drink.
Really nice ambience and you can go alfresco if you don't want the air con..

formattedAddress: No.1 Ground Floor, Lot 12168, Song Plaza (Jalan Song)
location.address: No.1 Ground Floor, Lot 12168, Song Plaza

tip.text: I love most of the food sold here and this is one of them.. Soupy Chee liaw noodles @ RM6 per bowl
Had seafood fried noodles here... Noodles was way too little compared to what I can get for the same price -Rm5 while the satay was ok. I found the ketupat a bit too soft though...

formattedAddress: Tabuan Stutong Commercial Centre (Jalan Setia Raja)

tip.text: You guys should try the nasi lemak here. At only RM 3.50, you get rice, an ample Amy of peanuts, sambal, slices of cucumber, salted fish and even a fried egg!
I recommend the pineapple rice here... Rather fragrant and tasty
Love the new LF5S here!! The screen is hugeee and seats rather comfortable. Best to watch box office movies too. Btw, Wed is movie day and tickets are half priced!
Wide variety of vegetarian dishes found here.  Love the Calzone pizza... Food is a bit pricy here though..
Love the soft cream puffs at Twinklepan... Go and try them
Definitely the best place to get different varieties of gong pia here... The minced pork n cheese one is highly recommended... Don't forget to try the Rojak here as they add in crispy yu char Kueh!!

tip.text: Yummy duck noodles can be found here! The meat is sooo tender! Greatly recommended....
